"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-news-world-1935934-putins-olympic-heroes-should-be\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Russian and Belarusian athletes who won medals at the Olympics should be stripped of them after failing to adhere to rules, a human rights group has claimed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9991105174935199, \"rank\": 0.0008537464841262278, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 14, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9911429806742461, \"rank\": 0.005713234966920669, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Global Rights Compliance (GRC) had claimed in the lead up to the gamesthat more than half of those set to appear had failed to adhere to rules imposed by theInternational Olympic Committee (IOC)on which their participation as neutral athletes hinged.\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rights\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Global Rights\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rights\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rights\"}, {\"begin\": 187, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\", \"score\": 0.5843297922483627, \"rank\": 0.711362338984042, \"text\": \"GRC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes competing as neutrals were prohibited from demonstrating support for theRussian warinUkraineand from having any contact with military or national security agencies, but GRC claims that this was ignored by many of those taking part.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\", \"score\": 0.5843297922483627, \"rank\": 0.711362338984042, \"text\": \"GRC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"31RussianandBelarusianathletes competed as neutral athletes with five going on to win medals in four events.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wayne Jordash KC, President of Global Rights Compliance, said, \\\"These Olympic Games were an opportunity for the IOC to affirm its commitments to peace, stability and human rights for all.\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen's_Counsel\", \"score\": 0.9979508395738326, \"rank\": 0.0011246075245895616, \"text\": \"KC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen's_Counsel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen's_Counsel\"}, {\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rights\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Global Rights\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rights\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rights\"}, {\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4434792948333525e-24, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Ukrainian Olympian's fury as Russian athletes at Paris 'feeding Putin's war'    \\\"Instead, despite receiving evidence showing that many athletes had contravened these principles, it buried its head in the sand.\\\"\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999979279437, \"rank\": 2.0589506082907643e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9991105174935199, \"rank\": 0.0008537464841262278, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999992333844813, \"rank\": 7.666159354194359e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1028, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1231425812889046e-20, \"text\": \"Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"GRC intends to lobby the IOC to strip the athletes of their medals, with the group claiming that they have damming evidence that all of the winners failed to adhere to the rules.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\", \"score\": 0.5843297922483627, \"rank\": 0.711362338984042, \"text\": \"GRC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_Rallycross\", \"dbpedia\": \"h